{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2015}} {{Infobox person | name = Bill Comrie | image = <!-- just the filename, without the File: or Image: prefix or enclosing [[brackets]] --> | alt = | caption = | birth_name = <!-- only use if different from name --> | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1950|06|29}} | birth_place = [[Winnipeg]], [[Manitoba]] | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{Death-date and age|death date†|birth date†}} --> | death_place = | nationality = Canadian | occupation = | years_active = | known_for = Founding [[The Brick]] | notable_works = }} '''William H. Comrie''' (born June 29, 1950<ref>http://www.canadianbusiness.com/business-strategy/live-learn-bill-comrie/</ref>) is a Canadian businessman. He is the founder of [[The Brick]], one of Canada's largest volume retailers of furniture, mattresses, appliances and home electronics. In 2009, Comrie's estimated personal net worth was $415 million. <ref>[http://www.cbc.ca/news/story/2009/11/19/consumer-richest-canadians-list.html Richest Canadians get richer - CBC News]</ref> Comrie is head of the '''Brick Group Income Fund'''.
Comrie was born in [[Winnipeg]], [[Manitoba]] and grew up in [[Edmonton]], [[Alberta]].<ref name=autogenerated1>[http://www.chfaweb.ca/e-roy2004.html Canadian Home Furnishings Alliance<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
He played with the [[Moose Jaw Canucks]], a [[Chicago Blackhawks]] farm team and later [[Edmonton Oil Kings]], but retired from hockey in 1968 to enter into the family furniture business following the death of his father Herb.<ref name=autogenerated1 />
In the spring of 2015 Comrie became a minority owner (and limited partner) of the [[Chicago Cubs]] baseball team.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ecker|first1=Danny|title=Two more Cubs minority investors revealed|url=http://www.chicagobusiness.com/article/20150303/BLOGS04/150309921/two-more-cubs-minority-investors-revealed|website=Crain's Chicago Business|publisher=chicagobusiness.com|accessdate=October 21, 2015|date=March 3, 2015}}</ref>
==Personal life== Comrie is the father of the professional ice hockey players [[Mike Comrie|Mike]], [[Paul Comrie|Paul]] and [[Eric Comrie]].<ref>[http://slam.canoe.ca/Slam/Columnists/Jones/2007/02/06/3540649-sun.html CANOE - SLAM! Sports - Columnists - Jones: Follow my leader]</ref>
