{{BLP sources|date=October 2012}} '''Firoze Madatally Manji''' (born 1950) is a Kenyan-born author, activist and editor-in-Chief.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.momentumconference.org/speaker-presentation/speaker/firoze-manji/presentation/which-america-are-you-today/index.html |title=Firoze Manji - Which America Are You Today - Momentum 2008 &#124; Tides Momentum |publisher=Momentumconference.org |date=2008-07-22 |accessdate=2012-10-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://company-director-check.co.uk/director/903296590 |title=Firoze Madatally Manji - free company director check. Director id 903296590 - Companies House Information |publisher=Company-director-check.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2012-10-22}}</ref> He is the founder and executive director of [[Fahamu]] and editor of Pambazuka Press, an online news magazine.<ref>{{cite web|author=Azad Essa |url=http://www.aljazeera.com/indepth/features/2012/03/2012311214730736224.html |title=Q&A: Does #Kony2012 do more harm than good? - Features |publisher=Al Jazeera English |date= |accessdate=2012-10-22}}</ref> He is also the former Africa director for [[Amnesty International]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blackademics.org/interview-archive/july-2007-interview-firoze-manji/ |title=July 2007 Interview: Firoze Manji |publisher=blackademics.org |date= |accessdate=2012-10-22}}</ref> and former CEO of the [[Aga Khan Foundation]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.african-writing.com/six/firozemanji.htm |title=African Writing Online; Fiction; Pindiwe Nkosi; Erode |publisher=African-writing.com |date= |accessdate=2012-10-22}}</ref>
==Background== Manji was born in [[Kenya]], to Kenya's "Biscuit Baron" [[Madatally Manji]] and his wife Fatima.<ref name="autogenerated1995">Manji, Madatally, Memoirs of a Biscuit Baron, East African Educational Publishers Ltd, Nairobi, 1995</ref> After obtaining a [[dentistry]] degree in the [[United Kingdom|UK]], he started his career as a dentist for a short time. He then began working as a dental researcher with the Kenya Medical Research Institute.<ref name="autogenerated1995"/> During this time he worked towards getting a Masters and PhD in [[dental surgery]]. He worked for the International Development Research Center throughout Africa and then the [[Aga Khan Foundation]] in the UK.
==Books== *''African Awakenings, The Emerging Revolutions'', 2011<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fahamubooks.org/book/?GCOI=90638100375050&fa=author&person_ID=4|title=African Awakening The Emerging Revolutions|publisher=Fahamubooks.org|accessdate=2012-10-22}}</ref> *''China's New Role in Africa and the South: A Search for a New Perspective'', 2008 *''From the Slave Trade to ‘Free’ Trade: How Trade Undermines Democracy and Justice in Africa'' (with Patrick Burnett)
