'''Pietro Ferrero''' (2 September 1898 – 2 March 1949) was the founder of [[Ferrero SpA]], an [[Italy|Italian]] [[confectionery]]  and [[chocolatier]] company.<ref>{{cite web|title=The story of Ferrero Group and its Mission|url=https://www.ferrero.com/the-ferrero-group/a-family-story|website=Ferrero Corporate|accessdate=16 April 2017}}</ref> His company invented [[Nutella]], a [[hazelnut]]-cream spread, which is now sold in over 160 countries. The famous [[Ferrero Rocher]]s are also made by his company, Ferrero, as were Tic-Tacs and various Kinder chocolates.<ref>{{cite web|last=Mitzman |first=Dany |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/magazine-27438001 |title=Nutella: How the world went nuts for a hazelnut spread - BBC News |website=Bbc.com |date=2014-05-18 |accessdate=2017-03-18}}</ref>

