{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2015}} {{Infobox newspaper | name =Puls Biznesu | logo = | image = | caption = | type = Daily business newspaper | format = | owners = Bonnier Business | founder = Dagens Industri | publisher = | editor = | chiefeditor = | assoceditor = | maneditor = | newseditor = | managingeditordesign = | campuseditor = | campuschief = | opeditor = | sportseditor = | photoeditor = | staff = | foundation = {{start date and age|1997}} | political = | language = [[Polish language|Polish]] | ceased publication = | headquarters = [[Warsaw]] | circulation = 10,539 (October 2016) | sister newspapers = | ISSN = | oclc = | website = }}
'''''Puls Biznesu''''' (lit. ''Business' Pulse'') is a [[Polish language|Polish-language]] daily newspaper devoted to business and economic issues.<ref>{{cite book|title=Poland Investment, Trade Laws and Regulations Handbook|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=A66K62NT3qkC&pg=PA240|accessdate=22 December 2013|date=November 2009|publisher=Int'l Business Publications|isbn=978-1-4330-7650-3|page=240}}</ref>
==History and profile== ''Puls Biznesu'' was established by Dagens Industri in 1997.<ref>{{cite book|author=Robert G. Picard|title=Media Product Portfolios: Issues in Management of Multiple Products and Services|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jOuxwVRdtVMC&pg=PA191|accessdate=22 December 2013|date=12 July 2005|publisher=Psychology Press|isbn=978-1-4106-1362-2|page=191}}</ref><ref name=pap>{{cite web|title=Press and publishers|url=http://en.poland.gov.pl/Press,and,publishers,7226.html|work=The Republic of Poland. Official website.|accessdate=22 December 2013}}</ref> It is published by Bonnier Business (Polska) company, a Polish branch of the Swedish [[Bonnier Group]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Puls Biznesu|url=http://www.bonnier.com/English-tags/Puls-Biznesu/|work=Bonnier|accessdate=22 December 2013}}</ref><ref name=obp/> The newspaper features daily thematic add-ons: Real estate (published on Tuesdays), business and technology (Wednesdays), transport and forwarding (Thursdays) and job and career (Fridays). The newspaper also owns a web portal intended for stock market investors.
''Puls Biznesu'' presents Gazele Biznesu awards to the Polish companies.<ref name=wil>{{cite web|title=Willis Awarded for Outstanding Business Growth in Poland|url=http://www.willis.com/Documents/Media_Room/Press_Releases/2006/Willis-Wins-Gazele-Biznesu-Award.pdf|work=Willis Group Holdings|accessdate=22 December 2013|location=London|format=News Release|date=25 May 2006}}</ref> The paper is the recipient of the 2004 Society for News Design award.<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Ally Palmer|author2=Terry Watson|title=The secrets of good design|journal=Strategy Report|date=June 2004|volume=3|issue=3|url=http://ideas.typepad.com/WANreport.pdf|accessdate=6 February 2015}}</ref> The daily was awarded by the Chamber of Press Publishers GrandFront 2010 prize for its front page on 12 April 2010.<ref>{{cite web|title=Best Front Page for Puls Biznesu|url=http://www.bonnier.com/news-press/News/2011/May/Best-Front-Page-for-Puls-Biznesu/|work=Bonnier|accessdate=22 December 2013|date=24 May 2011}}</ref>
The circulation of ''Puls Biznesu'' was 23,282 copies in January–February 2001.<ref name=obp>{{cite web|title=Polish national dailies - circulation and sales|url=http://www.obp.pl/03-raport/2001/dailies_numb.htm|publisher=OBP|accessdate=2 December 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070304172127/http://www.obp.pl/03-raport/2001/dailies_numb.htm|archivedate=4 March 2007|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The 2005 circulation of the daily was about 45,000 copies.<ref name=wil/> It was 20,399 copies in 2006.<ref>{{cite book|author1=Jesper Strömbäck|author2=Lynda Lee Kaid|title=The Handbook of Election News Coverage Around the World|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kF3ajMYnyeYC&pg=PA230|accessdate=22 December 2013|date=18 June 2008|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-0-203-88717-2|page=230}}</ref>
